The paper presents a novel approach for multi-robot path planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm is based on Dijkstra, which is a classic algorithm used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for finding the shortest path. The approach also involves managing split and merge situations, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm is deterministic and finds an optimal solution, which is a characteristic of machine learning (cs.MA) and optimization (cs.LG) algorithms.
